Köpm:fören. om’b., led. av lolkailstyr. v. Gbgs Hand :banks kont. i Kuingälv, not. publ. i Kungälv, ordf. i nykterh :nd, ordf. i Nödinge o. Starr-kärrs’ hyresndr.
translated: Högstedt, Karl, LL.B., lawyer, Kungälv, b. 30/9/02 in Färlöv, Kristianstad 1st district, son of Carl H. and Alma Ekdahl. Married in 1932 to Ingrid Colhander. Children: Ragnar b. 1934, Lennart b. 1937, Stig b. 1939, Olof b. 1944. Karl graduated from Kristianstad in 1923 and Lund with a law degree in 1929. He worked as a district court judge between 1929-1932 before becoming the owner of Kungälv law firm. He was a member of the Swedish Bar Association, the Chamber of Commerce, and the board of directors at Gothenburg's Handelsbank. He was also a public notary in Kungälv, chairman of the temperance society, and chairman of the housing associations in Nödinge and Starr-kärr.
